message_1: What is the order of the pole of the function f(z) = (z^2 - 1)/(z - 2)^3 at z = 2?
message_2: The order of the pole of the function f(z) = (z^2 - 1)/(z - 2)^3 at z = 2 is 3. This is because the denominator (z - 2)^3 has a zero of order 3 at z = 2, and the numerator (z^2 - 1) does not have a zero at z = 2.
